define a checkpoint index to identify where we currently are, encountering H always move index back to 'first' i.e. index=0  so fen at checkpoint[0]
encountering < always moves back to the current last saved checkpoint so checkpoint[index] saved as next fen
encountering << performs index = index-1 and then checkpoint[index] saved as fen
encountering <<< performend index = index-2 and then checkpoint[index] saved as fen
etc..

assume MoveToHome is signified by "H" this will involve appending the Home Fen, and updating the checkpoint index

assume SetBranchPoint/SaveCheckpoint is signified by "*" this triggers adding a word to the fen list later, but not appending a FEN itself
option is to always add a fen but then later remove adjacent duplicates

move to checkpoint will involve adding a fen to the list (which will be a repeat)

we might as well keep track of all checkpoints, but we will never need to return to future ones
so it makes sense to create our list of fens, and we use << <<< and < to determine how many back in our checkpoints list we move

* = add checkpoint here
< = back to last/current checkpoint
<< = back 2 checkpoints
H = go home (checkpoint 0)

